snippet.textDisplay: Idk if I had endometriosis when I was 13 but I felt like it did, in the summer of 2013, I had my period for like 50+days straight and it’s was heavy everyday it started in July end in mid September. I was only 13 so I didn’t know about period I thought it was normal. I had really intense migraines everyday, the slightest movement it found feel like my brain was going to explode, I felt tired all the time and extremely pale (I’m black to). I had a craving for paper and would chew on loads of it. Looking back on it I could have died, I loose a lot of blood 🩸 since I was bleeding heavily everyday for over 2months, if it wasn’t for the Grace of God idk where I would be. Idk if it was endometriosis but it sounds like it could be. I didn’t even tell my parents, I haven’t told anyone until now 😔 but it hasn’t happened since.

snippet.textDisplay: The past 6 years have been rough with mental health, school and family. But being weak doesn't make you weak; it makes you strong for being able to face it and expressing it. I've been a fan of you tati for 7years now and while I do not have the money to buy make up much, I watch all your videos because I love the way you carry yourself through thick and thin. Never hide the pain let it out and confide in people. You are all human! I wish all of you the best for your entire life!!! (:
